Codex Ignore File

Prevents Codex from loading large or irrelevant files during analysis.

This reduces token usage and speeds up repository scanning.

Node / package artifacts

node_modules/ package-lock.json pnpm-lock.yaml yarn.lock

Build outputs

dist/ build/ out/ .next/ .cache/

Logs

*.log logs/

Environment files

.env .env.local .env.*

Binary assets (not useful for code analysis)

.png .jpg .jpeg .gif .webp .mp3 .wav .ogg .mp4 .mov

Large game assets

assets/ textures/ audio/ music/ sounds/ maps/ tiles/ tokens/

Generated data

coverage/ storybook-static/

Git metadata

.git/ .gitignore

System files

.DS_Store Thumbs.db

Temporary files

tmp/ temp/ *.tmp

Documentation builds

docs/build/

Compiled TypeScript

*.js.map
